{{Top|leg|canon=Garbage chute}}
{{Quote|Ugh! Of course, it has to be a garbage pit. Well, let's go&hellip; No one ever said being a Jedi was glamorous.|[[Kyle Katarn]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Jedi Academy">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Jedi Academy]]''</ref>}}
'''Garbage pits''', also known as '''garbage chutes''', were pits used as trash dumps on [[Planet/Legends|planets]] and [[Space station/Legends|space stations]] across [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. [[Dianoga/Legends|Dianogas]] were known to inhabit garbage pits due to sightings on-board [[The Wheel/Legends|The Wheel]] and in a [[Garbage compactor/Legends|trash compactor]] aboard the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]],<ref name="Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope">{{Film|IV}}</ref> among other locations.

Garbage pits on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] were used to relieve the planet of its massive amounts of garbage through a system that launched garbage into deep space. Illegal races were commonly held in Coruscant garbage pits. Racers would put on wings and try to fly to the bottom of the pit, grab a scale off [[Garbage worm|giant worms]] that lived at the bottom of the pit, and fly back to the top of the pit and the other side without getting hit by the cannons. [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] participated in one of these races while being chased by a [[Blood Carver]] named [[Ke Daiv]]. [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] then followed him into the races to help.<ref name="Rogue Planet">''[[Rogue Planet]]''</ref>

